RATES
getRate()                    → Live rate from Quidax for any pair

ONRAMP
initiateRamp()               → Routes to bank or mobile money
initiateRampBankTransfer()   → NGN — POST /initiate
initiateRampMobileMoney()    → GHS — POST /initiate + /initiate_mobile_money
confirmRamp()                → NGN only — POST /confirm → bank details
verifyMobileMoneyOtp()       → GHS OTP flow — POST /verify_mobile_money_otp
shapeAsPayments()            → Maps response to existing payments object

OFFRAMP
initiateOfframp()            → POST /initiate
confirmOfframp()             → POST /confirm → Quidax deposit address
addOfframpPayoutAccount()    → POST /bank_account → attach NGN/GHS account
shapeOfframpAsPayments()     → Maps response to existing crypto object

HELPERS
getUser()                    → Fetch user from DB
getNetwork()                 → bep20 for USDT, base for USDC
getPair()                    → usdtngn, usdcghs etc
getFiatConfig()              → Channel + currency code per fiat
verifyWebhookSignature()     → Validate incoming Quidax webhooks




 initOnramp()              initOfframp()
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Order type          SELL                      BUY
Wallet needed?       Yes — from pool           No
Quidax calls         initiate + confirm        initiate + confirm + bank_account
Returns to user      Bank account / momo       Crypto deposit address
triggerAddress       deposit wallet address    null
Webhook detects via  Tatum/Moralis             Quidax merchant_reference


preActions()                          ← entry point, reserves slot, fetches order
    ↓
    ├── order.isSynthetic === true
    │       ↓
    │   handleSyntheticPreActions()
    │       ↓
    │   setUpSyntheticUser()          ← no wallets
    │       ↓
    │       ├── type === SELL → initOnramp()   ← gets wallet from pool
    │       └── type === BUY  → initOfframp()  ← no wallet at all
    │       ↓
    │   awaiting.update() + postDetails.create()
    │
    └── order.isSynthetic === false
            ↓
        handleNormalPreActions()      ← your exact existing code, untouched
            ↓
        setUpUser()                   ← creates base + quote wallets
            ↓
        awaiting.update() + postDetails.create()


EVENT                    HANDLER                      RESULT
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
on_ramp.processing       handleOnrampProcessing()     status → PROCESSING
on_ramp.completed        handleOnrampCompleted()      status → CONFIRMING
                                                       (Tatum finishes it)
off_ramp.processing       handleOfframpProcessing()    status → PROCESSING
off_ramp.completed       handleOfframpCompleted()     status → COMPLETED
                                                       (we finish it here)
on/off_ramp.failed       handleRampFailed()           status → FAILED

The key difference — onramp hands off to Tatum/Moralis for the final credit, while offramp completes itself right here in the webhook since there's no on-chain deposit to wait for on our side (Quidax already converted and paid out).


1. ramp.worker.ts              ✅ creates synthetic orders
2. liquidityRamp.service.ts    ✅ talks to Quidax
3. setUpSyntheticUser()        ✅ minimal user setup
4. initOnramp()                ✅ onramp-specific logic
5. initOfframp()               ✅ offramp-specific logic
6. preActions() rewired        ✅ routes synthetic vs normal
7. webhook handler             ✅ processes Quidax events